    <qtext><![CDATA[
        <h2>Chicken and corn soup</h2>

        <u>Ingredients</u>

        <ul>
            <li>1.5 L water</li>
            <li>500 g chicken drumsticks</li>
            <li>one onion</li>
            <li>half a bunch spring onions</li>
            <li>440 gm canned cream corn</li>
            <li>2 chicken stock cubes</li>
            <li>15 mL soy sauce</li>
        </ul>

        <u>Method</u>
        <p>
        Place water and chicken in saucepan.  Add sliced onion.  <br />
        Simmer for 30 minutes.  Strain the liquid into a large bowl.  <br />
        Skin and chop chicken, discarding bones.  Returned chicken and liquid to saucepan.  <br />
        Finely slice spring onions, and add, along with the corn.  Add stock cubes and soy sauce.  <br />
        Stir until boiling.  Serve in deep plates while very hot. SERVES 4.  <br />
        </p>
        ]]>
    </qtext>
